tion, and I don't know if you'll want to publish it. So Ashish's suggestion=
 of using the github wiki makes more sense, although really, my ideal would=
 be something like a 'wiki.ocaml.org', where the wiki is a proper wikimedia=
-style wiki, much like wiki.python.org or wiki.xenproject.org.
>=20
> In my opinion, there's room for both the structured articles currently on=
 ocaml.org and a less rigid, evolving centralized wiki. We have the former,=
 but not the latter.

