e wiki is where user input goes.=20=20

Overall, I get the feeling that your arguments start with the fact that you=
 want a wiki but the things you state in support of it are just as applicab=
le to the current site.  The one thing that does stand out is the ability t=
o create work-in-progress content to share with others.  I like Ashish's su=
ggestion of using the github wiki and as he pointed out, you (or anyone) ca=
n immediately begin putting content there, structuring it however you feel =
